<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PTM6.6.5">
<l>aṉṟulaka mūṉṟiṉaiyu maḷantu vēṟō rariyuruvā yiraṇiyaṉa tākaṅ kīṇṭu</l>
<l>veṉṟavaṉai viṇṇulakil celavuyt tāṟku viruntāvīr mēleḻuntu vilaṅkal pāyntu</l>
<l>poṉcitaṟi maṇikoṇarntu karaimēl cintip pulamparantu nilamparakkum poṉṉi nāṭaṉ</l>
<l>teṉtamiḻaṉ vaṭapulakkōṉ cōḻaṉ cērnta tirunaṟaiyūr maṇimāṭañ cērmiṉ kaḷē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>You who would become [heavenly] guests for him who,</l>
<l rend="indent">having once measured the three worlds, in another form as a lion,</l>
<l>Drove Hiraṇya to go to the heavenly world,</l>
<l rend="indent">having conquered [him] and split his chest,</l>
<l>Gather at the beautiful raised shrine in Tirunaṟaiyūr, where came the Cōḻa,</l>
<l rend="indent">who is the one of the Tamils in the South</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] the king of the northern land,</l>
<l>The lord of the land of the Poṉṉi [River] which, rising from peaks,</l>
<l rend="indent">gushing down mountains, scattering gold, bringing jewels</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] strewing [them] on the shore, covering the fields,</l>
<l rend="indent">spreads over the land.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
